# CLAUDE.md — [Project Name]

## Core behavior rules

Minimal footprint. Only touch files directly related to the task. Do not refactor adjacent code, add comments to code you didn't change, or improve things "while you're in there."

Do not ask for confirmation before running shell commands, creating files, or making edits. Just do it and report what you did.

When you encounter an error, debug in four phases: reproduce, isolate, root cause, fix. No shotgun debugging.

Never claim work is done without evidence. Run the verification. Show the output.

## Task management

At the start of each session, read tasks/current-task.md if it exists.
After any significant progress, update tasks/current-task.md with: what you just did, what's next, any blockers.

## Routing

For file search: use glob and grep, not Agent.
For multi-step tasks with multiple files: break into steps and confirm after each.
For research: summarize findings before acting on them.

## Code conventions

[Add your project-specific conventions here]

## What NOT to do

- Don't add comments to code you didn't change
- Don't refactor adjacent code "while you're in there"
- Don't add error handling for impossible scenarios
- Don't create utility files for one-time operations
- Don't guess API contracts — check docs first
